</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=istari@graffeswizardcompilation>Istari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 293<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/27/03 11:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> fun?</span><hr size=1> I don't think this nuke is fun. sure it has a huge damage variance, but i'd prolly have more fun with a firework that shot &quot;WIZARDS &gt; DRUIDS&quot;(/duck I &lt;3 druids: really!) into the air as a particle effect sign. <br>
<br>
I'll look at raw speed of damage:<br>
Base avg hit of som: 2100 cast time: 8.25<br>
Base hit of AT: 2305 cast time: 9.25<br>
<br>
SOM: 2100/8.25 = 254.54<br>
AT: 2305/9.25 = 249.19<br>
...resulting in a 2% damage boost for using SOM for quick damage.<br>
hasted:<br>
2100/5.85 = 359<br>
2305/6.45 = 357<br>
Then you observe that due to the faster cast time(recast is not hasted), the difference shrinks to .05% difference! then I ask: is there any purpose to this spell? Its fast damage is the same as AT, its ratio inferior, its resist far inferior. I think making it a draught would breathe some unique power into this spell, while being balanced: a fast damage draught that's of an inferior ratio. a change like this wouldn't be a bad thing, some change should be made to the spell to at least make it useful somewhere.<br>
<br>
as for draughts and resists... in the elemental planes, even eci in fire, draughts can have a sizable resist rate to a raid mob that doesnt have the crap debuffed out of it anyway. a big ice nuke should be here anyway. having some resists blocked from our spell types is silly- for instance, I don't see why we don't get a MR based rain either, which mages do or that we're outdone for nukes in some categoris by other classes... shrug. something worthy should be made of that nuke, right now there's nothing functionally superior about it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quineloe>Quineloe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1748<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/27/03 11:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shock of Magic should be made draught like!</span><hr size=1> There's no point at all in SOM having a +20 resist check. It makes the spell basically worthless without Tash or other debuffs, but the TO DO list for SOE is endless anyways. <p>Sage Quineloe<br>
